Distribution. This species is known from two localities in the upper Kerio River system (the type locality on Barwessa River (asterisk,
Fig. 1
) and in the Kerio River at Chebloch Gorge (cross,
Fig. 1
)) and is likely endemic to the system. This species was abundant in the medium rapids upstream from the road crossing (Chebloch Gorge) and were aggregated near the larger boulders. It is likely that further sampling efforts within the upper Kerio River system will reveal addition populations.
